1
00:00:00,218 --> 00:00:01,964
Before Transformers, sequence models

2
00:00:01,964 --> 00:00:04,291
read text one token at a time, so

3
00:00:04,291 --> 00:00:05,891
long-range links were slow and

4
00:00:05,891 --> 00:00:06,618
fragile.

5
00:00:06,836 --> 00:00:08,508
Self-attention changed that: every

6
00:00:08,508 --> 00:00:09,890
token can look directly at every

7
00:00:09,890 --> 00:00:11,418
other token in the sequence.

8
00:00:11,636 --> 00:00:13,599
Each token starts as an embedding

9
00:00:13,599 --> 00:00:15,854
plus a positional encoding, so the

10
00:00:15,854 --> 00:00:17,672
model knows meaning and order.

11
00:00:17,889 --> 00:00:19,708
From that matrix X, it learns

12
00:00:19,708 --> 00:00:22,035
queries, keys, and values.

13
00:00:22,253 --> 00:00:24,289
Queries seek, keys match, and values

14
00:00:24,289 --> 00:00:26,035
carry the information forward.

15
00:00:26,253 --> 00:00:28,435
The core step is QK transpose over

16
00:00:28,435 --> 00:00:30,835
root d-k, then softmax, then

17
00:00:30,835 --> 00:00:32,289
a weighted mix of V.

18
00:00:32,506 --> 00:00:33,670
Those weights make meaning

19
00:00:33,670 --> 00:00:35,706
contextual, and multi-head attention

20
00:00:35,706 --> 00:00:37,452
lets different heads track different

21
00:00:37,452 --> 00:00:38,834
relationships at once.

22
00:00:39,052 --> 00:00:41,016
Stacked blocks train in parallel,

23
00:00:41,016 --> 00:00:42,907
but attention still has a quadratic

24
00:00:42,907 --> 00:00:43,707
cost.
